newsitem.title: UK: NWE oil products weaken on lacklustre demand.
newsitem.headline: NWE oil products weaken on lacklustre demand.

text.p: NWE oil products weakened on Wednesday, with many sectors hit by feeble buying interest, traders said.
Gas oil slid on easier IPE futures and mild weather and lack of buying interest hit premiums. A barge of storage material heating oil traded at Nov IPE flat fob ARA, $1 easier.
Gasoline fell $2 a tonne on weaker crude and U.S gasoline. Eurograde barges traded lower at $235.50 fob ARA at the close. Naphtha eased with a barge traded at cif quotes high +25 cents fob ARA.
